# TypeScript Standards

## Module System

- Use ES modules (`import`/`export`), not CommonJS
- Use `.js` extension in imports for compiled output: `from "./foo.js"`

## Style

- Functional style; avoid class components
- Prefer `async`/`await` over raw Promises

## Error Handling

- Use typed errors from `mercury-fork/src/agent/container-error.ts`
- Log errors with context; avoid empty catch blocks

```typescript
// BAD
try { await fetchData(); } catch (e) {}

// GOOD
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (e) {
  logger.error("Failed to fetch", { error: e });
  throw new DataFetchError("Unable to retrieve data", { cause: e });
}
```

## Config

- All configuration via env vars
- Parse with Zod in `mercury-fork/src/config.ts`
- Never hardcode secrets
